  ;; ── Design notes ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
  (text "AUDIO OUTPUT DESIGN NOTES:\n\n1) MAX98357A receives I2S from ESP32 (separate I2S port from ES7243E ADC)\n   ESP32 plays decoded/passthrough audio back via I2S DAC port\n   BCLK/LRCK shared with ES7243E but data lines are separate\n   SD_MODE = HIGH → Left channel output only (mono speaker)\n   SD_MODE = LOW  → Amplifier shutdown (BT connected = speaker mute)\n   SD_MODE = FLOAT → Left+Right mix to mono (use for mono speaker)\n   Controlled by ESP32 GPIO33 (AMP_SD)\n\n2) Power for PVDD:\n   Connect to VBAT (3.7V LiPo) for maximum output power ~1.4W @ 8Ω\n   MAX output voltage limited by supply: Pout ≈ (Vbat²)/(2×Rload)\n\n3) Output EMI filter required for Class-D:\n   L3/L4 = 10µH, C23/C24 = 100nF to GND on each BTL output\n   DO NOT connect OUT+ or OUT- directly to GND\n   DO NOT add series capacitor on BTL output (differential output)\n\n4) Speaker SPK1: 8Ω / 1W, 1511 type (20mm diameter)\n   Connect via 2-pin JST or solder pads\n\n5) Headphone Jack J3 (optional analog output):\n   SI4732 LOUT/ROUT → 100µF AC couple → TRS tip/ring\n   Detect pin: NC when no HP, pulled LOW when HP inserted\n   Detect → ESP32 GPIO (firmware auto-mutes AMP when HP plugged in)\n   This bypasses MAX98357A entirely for the headphone path\n\n6) Bluetooth audio flow:\n   SI4732 analog → ES7243E (ADC) → ESP32 I2S in → A2DP encode → BT TX\n   When BT connected: AMP_SD = LOW (speaker off)\n   When BT disconnected: AMP_SD = HIGH (speaker on)\n\n7) BT Status LED: Blue LED, 100Ω series, driven by GPIO34 (open-drain)\n   OFF = BT disabled, BLINK = pairing, ON = connected"
    (at 210 90)
    (effects (font (size 1.7 1.7)) (justify left))
  )
)
